<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-307-518  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 307 518.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computers in Healthcare  April 1990 v11 n4 p43(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Clinical workstations aimed at nursing shortages and productivity.andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>IBM and Spectrum Healthcare Solutions introduce the IBM 7690Clinical Workstation, a bedside, point-of-care workstation that isdesigned to assist healthcare practitioners in their daily effortsto manage workflow.andP;  The workstation, which includes Spectrum'sClinical Series software, is designed for installation in thepatient's hospital room.andP;  The nurse can input patient care data atthe point-of-service and doctors and other nurses can access theinformation from any PS/2 on the hospital network.andP;  Benefitsinclude additional nursing productivity, more time for patientcare, planning, staffing and scheduling assistance and more.andO;Touch screen technology facilitates quick data access.andP;  Nursingapplications were developed first because of the critical natureof needs.andP;  Studies are underway to determine which areas needaddressing next.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (products)Spectrum Healthcare Solutions (products).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   IBM 7690 Clinical Workstation (usage).andO;Topic:     Medical RecordsAutomation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>